          "rationale": "Texas law requires a person who prepares or serves food (including a catering operation) to hold a food establishment permit. The state DSHS permit under Tex. Health & Safety Code 437.0055 is the residual permit that applies where no county or public health district issues one, renewed every two years; in most cities and counties the operative permit is the LOCAL city/county/public-health-district food permit. Check your local health department.",
          "userAction": "Ask this caterer for its current food establishment permit (from the local health department where one exists, otherwise the Texas DSHS permit)."
        }
