          "rationale": "Texas law requires a food establishment that handles unpackaged food needing temperature control to have at least one Certified Food Protection Manager present during all hours of operation, with the certificate posted for consumers (25 TAC 228.31; Tex. Health & Safety Code ch. 438). The certificate is earned by passing an accredited exam and renewed by re-examination; the validity period is set by the accrediting program.",
