            "section": "Tex. Alcoholic Beverage Code 11.01, 28.01, 28.19, 11.09, 11.11",
            "url": "https://statutes.capitol.texas.gov/Docs/AL/htm/AL.28.htm",
            "effectiveDateOfText": "current as displayed (fetched 2026-07-07); reflects HB 1545 (2019) consolidation",
            "verifiedDate": "2026-07-07"
          },
          "rationale": "Texas law requires a caterer that itself sells or serves alcoholic beverages to hold the appropriate TABC retail permit; for distilled-spirit service that is a Mixed Beverage Permit, exercised at off-site events through its temporary-location authority (Tex. Alcoholic Beverage Code 28.19). The permit expires on its second anniversary (11.09), and a Chapter 28 permit requires a conduct surety bond ($5,000; $10,000 within 1,000 ft of a school). Many caterers do not hold their own permit where the venue or a licensed bar service provides the alcohol.",
          "userAction": "If this caterer provides the alcohol at events, ask for its current TABC permit (renewed every two years)."
        }
